Inza WENDELEN, as Administratrix of the Estate of Charles Wendelen, deceased, Plaintiff-Appellant, v. COMMANDER LARABEE MILLING COMPANY, Defendant-Respondent. No. 144, Docket 21857. United States Court of Appeals Second Circuit. Argued Feb. 13, 1951. Decided March 5, 1951. William J. Brock, Buffalo, N. Y., Edward H. Kavinoky, Buffalo, N. Y., of counsel, for Inza Wendelen, as Admin-istratrix of Estate of Charles Wendelen, deceased, plaintiff-appellant. Brown, Kelly, Turner & Symons, Buffalo, N. Y., John E. Leach, Buffalo, N. Y., of counsel, for Commander Larabee Milling Co., defendant-appellee.

Before AUGUSTUS N. HAND, CHASE and CLARK, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Affirmed on the opinion of Knight, J., in the court below. 96 F.Supp. 92.
